<paragraph blockId="19.[123,652,384,788]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
ETYMOLOGY: The name is a combination of 
<emphasis box="[159,228,707,730]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">leptos</emphasis>
(Greek λeπτóơ, or thin, lean) and the genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" box="[322,424,736,759]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Gnoriste" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,424,736,759]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Gnoriste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new name is feminine.
</paragraph>
